{% extends 'layouts/page.njk' %}

{% block content %}
  {{ appHeading({
    text: heading,
    caption: "GOV.UK Content Review"
  }) }}

  <div class="govuk-grid-row">
    <div class="govuk-grid-column-two-thirds">
      <div class="govuk-body" data-testid="app-page-body">
        <p class="govuk-body-l">
          AI-powered content review tool to help ensure your content meets GOV.UK standards.
        </p>
        
        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">What this tool does</h2>
        <p>The Content Review Tool helps you:</p>
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
          <li>Review content for plain English and clarity</li>
          <li>Check compliance with GOV.UK style guidelines</li>
          <li>Identify areas for improvement in readability</li>
          <li>Get AI-powered suggestions for better content</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">How to use this tool</h2>
        <p>Simply paste or type your content in the text area on the home page, and the AI will review it against GOV.UK standards and provide detailed feedback.</p>

        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">How the AI reviews your content</h2>
        <p>The AI evaluates your content against 5 key categories:</p>

        <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">1. Plain English</h3>
        <p>The AI checks for:</p>
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
          <li>Use of clear, simple language and avoidance of jargon</li>
          <li>Sentence length (aiming for 15-20 words average)</li>
          <li>GOV.UK "words to avoid" (e.g., "utilise", "facilitate", "going forward")</li>
          <li>Complex words that could be simplified</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">2. Clarity & Structure</h3>
        <p>The AI assesses:</p>
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
          <li>Logical flow and organization of ideas</li>
          <li>Content scannability and readability</li>
          <li>User-focused approach (starting with what matters most to users)</li>
          <li>Passive voice usage (active voice is preferred)</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">3. Accessibility</h3>
        <p>The AI evaluates:</p>
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
          <li>Language complexity and reading age</li>
          <li>Unexplained technical terms and jargon</li>
          <li>Language barriers for users with different abilities</li>
          <li>Overall inclusivity of the content</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">4. GOV.UK Style Compliance</h3>
        <p>The AI checks for:</p>
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
          <li>Adherence to GOV.UK style guide for language and tone</li>
          <li>Correct use of numerals vs words (e.g., "9am", not "nine o'clock")</li>
          <li>Appropriate voice and tone for government content</li>
          <li>Avoidance of corporate speak and buzzwords</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">5. Content Completeness</h3>
        <p>The AI assesses whether:</p>
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
          <li>All necessary information is included</li>
          <li>Instructions are clear and actionable</li>
          <li>There are any gaps in the explanation</li>
          <li>The content length is appropriate for the purpose</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="govuk-inset-text">
          <p><strong>Note:</strong> The AI reviews plain text only. It cannot evaluate visual formatting elements like headings, lists, or links. Focus is on language quality and content structure.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Review output</h2>
        <p>After reviewing your content, the AI provides:</p>
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
          <li>A summary with scores for each of the 5 categories</li>
          <li>Your original content with color-coded highlights showing specific issues</li>
          <li>Top 5 priority improvements with examples and suggestions</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

{% endblock %}
